## Tech stack

- **Framework:** [Nuxt 4](https://nuxt.com/) (Vue 3, TypeScript)
- **Styling:** [Tailwind CSS 4](https://tailwindcss.com/)
- **UI Components:** [Volt](https://volt.primevue.org/) (PrimeVue + Tailwind)
- **Database:** PostgreSQL with [Kysely](https://kysely.dev/) (type-safe query builder)
- **Validation:** [Zod](https://zod.dev/)
- **Auth:** [nuxt-auth-utils](https://github.com/atinux/nuxt-auth-utils) (session-based{% if include_google_oauth %}, Google OAuth{% endif %})
- **Testing:** [Vitest](https://vitest.dev/) with transaction-based DB isolation
- **Package Manager:** Yarn 4
- **Node:** 22+

## Getting started

```bash
# Install dependencies
yarn install

# Start the dev server
yarn dev
```

The app runs at http://localhost:3000.

### Environment variables

Copy `.env.example` to `.env` and fill in the values:

| Variable | Description |
|---|---|
| `NUXT_DATABASE_URL` | PostgreSQL connection string |
| `NUXT_SESSION_PASSWORD` | Secret for signing session cookies |
{% if include_google_oauth %}| `NUXT_OAUTH_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID` | Google OAuth client ID |
| `NUXT_OAUTH_GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET` | Google OAuth client secret |
{% endif %}
## Database

```bash
# Run pending migrations
yarn db:migrate

# Rollback the last migration
yarn db:migrate:down

# Create a new migration
yarn db:migrate:make <name>

# Regenerate TypeScript types from the database schema
yarn db:codegen
```

After creating or modifying tables, run `yarn db:codegen` to keep the generated types in `server/db/db.d.ts` up to date.

## Testing

Backend tests run against a real PostgreSQL database (`{{ database_name }}-test`). Each test runs inside a transaction that is rolled back automatically, so tests are fast and fully isolated.

```bash
# Run backend tests (watch mode)
yarn test

# Run backend tests once
yarn test:run

# Run frontend tests (watch mode)
yarn test:frontend

# Run frontend tests once
yarn test:frontend:run
```

